-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Wed Jan 15, 2014 10:58PM EST
-- None



Jan 16 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* Charter Communications Inc <CHTR.O> reached out to Comcast Corp <CMCSA.O> this week about teaming up to buy Time Warner Cable Inc <TWC.N>, after the larger rival rejected its $37.3 billion takeover bid, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0KP293]  * A number of Time Warner Cable <TWC.N> shareholders would support a merger with Charter Communications Inc <CHTR.O> if Charter raises its current bid for the larger rival to $41 billion or more, according to people close to the matter.[ID:nL2N0KP1QM]  * Microsoft Corp <MSFT.O> is considering Ericsson AB <ERICb.ST> Chief Executive Hans Vestberg as a possible successor to outgoing CEO Steve Ballmer, Bloomberg cited sources briefed on the software giant's executive search as saying on Wednesday.[ID:nL2N0KQ02D]  * U.S. defense contractor Altegrity Inc [AGRTY.UL] has hired restructuring advisers as it contends with a debt burden of about $1.8 billion, the Wall Street Journal reported on Wednesday, citing people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL3N0KQ0ZK]  * The Carlyle Group <CG.O> has all but clinched a deal to buy Johnson & Johnson's <JNJ.N> clinical testing arm for about $4.1 billion after several weeks of negotiations, a person briefed on the matter said on Wednesday, New York Times reported. (http://r.reuters.com/zuv95v)